  "prompt": "How can evaporated milk be substituted for condensed milk?",
  "response": "Evaporated milk and condensed milk are similar, but they are not exactly the same and are not perfectly interchangeable due to their differences in sweetness and texture. Condensed milk is sweetened, while evaporated milk is not.\n\nIf you need to substitute evaporated milk for condensed milk, you can add sugar to evaporated milk to approximate the sweetness and consistency of condensed milk. Here\u2019s a general guideline:\n\n1. **Sugar Addition**: For every 1 cup of evaporated milk, add approximately 1 \u00bc to 1 \u00bd cups of granulated sugar.\n2. **Mix Thoroughly**: Heat the mixture slowly and stir until the sugar is completely dissolved. Let the mixture cool before using it in recipes that call for condensed milk.\n\nKeep in mind that the flavor profile might still be slightly different, but for many recipes, this substitution can work adequately.",
